 "components": {
  "task_instruction": "You are a precise text classifier. Read the input text and assign it to exactly one of the categories defined below.",
  "label::alarm_query": "",
  "label::alarm_set": "This category is for setting a generic alert or alarm to sound at a specific time or after a certain duration, without linking it to a specific action or event. Use alarm_set for simple requests like \"set an alarm\" or \"wake me up\" at a time, where no particular event or reminder is described. If the request specifies an action to be reminded about at a certain time (e.g., \"remind me to...\"), choose calendar_set instead.",
  "label::calendar_query": "",
  "label::calendar_remove": "",
  "label::calendar_set": "Events, reminders, and appointments that are scheduled for a specific future date or time belong in this category. This includes requests to \"remind me\" or \"put on my calendar,\" whether for meetings, deadlines, or actions to perform at a later point. If the request involves remembering an activity at a specific future moment (even something like \"remind me to take coffee off stove in ten minutes\"), choose calendar_set; if it's just a generic alarm or wakeup with no action or event, choose alarm_set.",
  "label::cooking_recipe": "",
  "label::datetime_query": "",
  "label::email_query": "",
  "label::email_sendemail": "",
  "label::general_quirky": "For questions or requests that don't fit any of the defined categories, including open-ended, personal, or fun queries (e.g., \"Tell me about...,\" \"What's the best...,\" or general trivia), assign general_quirky. If the text asks for information, opinions, or narratives not focused on a location to visit or a clear fact/definition, use this category. Use general_quirky instead of recommendation_locations for subjective or descriptive requests about locations without a request for recommendations or suggestions.",
  "label::iot_hue_lightoff": "",
  "label::lists_createoradd": "",
  "label::lists_query": "",
  "label::lists_remove": "",
  "label::music_query": "",
  "label::news_query": "",
  "label::play_audiobook": "",
  "label::play_music": "",
  "label::play_podcasts": "",
  "label::play_radio": "",
  "label::qa_currency": "",
  "label::qa_definition": "",
  "label::qa_factoid": "",
  "label::qa_stock": "",
  "label::recommendation_events": "",
  "label::recommendation_locations": "Recommendation_locations is for requests that specifically ask for suggestions or recommendations of places to go or visit (e.g., \"Can you suggest a good restaurant nearby?\"). If the user asks about the best or recommended locations and clearly wants a list of options or advice on where to go, choose this. If the request is more general, asking for facts, descriptions, or narratives about a location (without seeking suggestions), do not use this category—use general_quirky or another appropriate label instead.",
  "label::social_post": "",
  "label::takeaway_order": "",
  "label::transport_query": "",
  "label::weather_query": "",
  "boundary_rules": ""
 },
